South Africa's Lungi Ngidi. AFP/Lakruwan Wanniarachchi JOHANNESBURG - South African bowler, Lungi Ngidi has announced that he will be joining the Roc Nation Sports family. The 24-year-old is the first cricketer to join the global sports management company. READ: Profile: Who is Lungi Ngidi "Proud to be the first cricketer to join the family. Excited for this new chapter @rocnationsports," he said in a post on Twitter. He joins Springbok captain, Siya Kolisi and Rugby World Cup-winner, Cheslin Kolbe as part of the Roc Nation family.